ichi]]\n| publisher       = [[Shueisha]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher\n| NA  = [[Viz Media]]\n}}\n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]]'' \n| imprint         = [[Jump Comics]]\n| magazine        = [[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump]]\n| magazine_en     = {{English manga magazines\n| NA  = [[Weekly Shonen Jump (American magazine)|Weekly Shonen Jump]]\n}}\n| published       = \n| first           = March 6, 2017\n| volumes         = 14\n| volume_list     = List of Dr. Stone chapters\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = tv series\n| title           = \n| director        = Shinya Iino \n| writer          = Yuichiro Kido\n| music           = [[Tatsuya Kato]]<br/>Hiroaki Tsutsumi<br/>Yuki Kanesaka\n| studio          = [[TMS Entertainment|TMS/8PAN]]\n| licensee        = {{English anime licensee|NA=[[Crunchyroll]]<br/>[[Funimation]]}}\n| network         = [[Tokyo MX]], [[Kyoto Broadcasting System|KBS]], [[Sun Television|SUN]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]], [[Television Hokkaido|TVh]], [[Tohoku Broadcasting Company|TBC]], [[Aichi Television Broadcasting|TVA]], [[TVQ Kyushu Broadcasting|TVQ]]\n| network_en      = {{English anime network\n | US = [[Adult Swim]] ([[Toonami]])}}\n| first           = July 5, 2019\n| last            = present\n| episodes        = 24\n| episode_list    = List of Dr. Stone episodes\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| title           = Dr. Stone Reboot: Byakuya\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Boichi\n| illustrator     = \n| publisher       = Shueisha\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher\n| NA  = Viz Media\n}}\n| demographic     = ''Sh\u014dnen'' \n| imprint         = Jump Comics\n| magazine        = Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump\n| magazine_en     = \n| first           = October 28, 2019\n| last          = December 23, 2019\n| volumes         = 1\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Dr. Stone'''''|\u30c9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30f3|Dokut\u0101 Sut\u014dn|lead=yes}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series written by [[Riichiro Inagaki]] and illustrated by [[Boichi]], serialized in ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump]]'' since March 6, 2017 with the individual chapters collected and published by [[Shueisha]] into thirteen ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes {{as of|2019|November|lc=yes}}. \n\n[[Viz Media]] licensed the manga in North America. Shueisha began to simulpublish the series in English on the website and app [[Manga Plus]] since January 2019. \n\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[TMS Entertainment]] aired from July 2019 to December 2019. A second season of the anime series focused on the \"Stone Wars\" arc of the manga series was announced at the end of the 24th and final episode of the first season.\n\n==Plot==\n{{Main article|List of Dr. Stone characters}}\n3,700 years after a mysterious flash of light [[Petrifaction in mythology and fiction|petrified]] the human population, a teenage genius named Senku Ishigami is suddenly revived to find himself in a world where all traces of human civilization have been eroded by time. Senku sets up a basecamp and begins to study the petrified humans. Senku learns his revival was made possible with [[nitric acid]], reviving his friend Taiju Oki, their classmate Yuzuriha Ogawa, and a martial artist named Tsukasa Shishio to rebuild their civilization. Tsukasa opposes Senku's idea of forming a new scientific civilization and instead desires a new order to the world base on power. Nearly killing Senku, Tsukasa leaves and begins his own faction of the stone world.\n\n\nSenku then discovers a tribe of people already living on the planet and sees this as an opportunity to create his kingdom of science. The town is originally hesitant, but eventually learn the benefits of science to their survival. Over time, Senku becomes more trusted by the town, eventually being taught of their past to discover that the village was started by Senku's father figure as well as 5 other astronauts who happened to be in space at the time of petrification. Together with his new villager friends, Senku engages a Stone War with Tsukasa's clan. After Senku's Kingdom of Science wins, they end up facing a new enemy in a tribe known as the Petrification Kingdom, who possess the device used to petrify the world 3,700 years ago.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n{{See also|List of Dr. Stone chapters}}\nWritten by [[Riichiro Inagaki]] and illustrated by [[Boichi]], ''Dr. Stone'' was launched in the 14th issue of [[Shueisha]]'s ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump]]'' on March 6, 2017.<ref name=shonenjumpmag>{{cite web |title=Shonen Jump Magazine to Launch 6 New Series By Kuroko's Basketball, Beelzebub, More Authors |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-01-26/shonen-jump-magazine-to-launch-6-new-series-by-kuroko-basketball-beelzebub-more-authors/.111485 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref> It was one from a number of story proposals Inagaki brought to his editor, who chose it because he had no idea how it would develop. Boichi, who was looking for a story to work on, was approached around the time Inagaki (a fan of his art) finished the [[storyboard]]s for chapter 3.<ref>{{Cite web|title=\"The Making of a Jump Manga!\" \u2014 Dr. STONE|url=https://mangaplus.shueisha.co.jp/web_pages/216/|department=Project: Interviewing editors at ''MangaPlus'' (vol. 4) |work=[[Manga Plus]]|publisher=[[Shueisha]]}}</ref> \n\nAt their panel at [[Anime Boston]], [[Viz Media]] announced their license of the manga, and the first volume was published in September 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Viz Licenses Dragon Ball's Yamcha Spinoff, Ao Haru Ride, Radiant Manga, More |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-03-30/viz-licenses-dragon-ball-yamcha-spinoff-ao-haru-ride-radiant-manga-more/.129742 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Viz Media to Release Dr. Stone Manga in Print |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2018-03-02/viz-media-to-release-dr-stone-manga-in-print/.128482 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref> Shueisha began to simulpublish the series in English on the website and app [[Manga Plus]] in January 2019.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Shueisha Launches Free Global MANGA Plus Service |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-27/shueisha-launches-free-global-manga-plus-service/.142634 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 23, 2019 |date=January 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2019, it was announced that a spin-off miniseries with nine chapters called ''Dr. Stone Reboot: Byakuya'' would debut on October 28 in the issue #48 of Shueisha's ''Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump'' with story and art by Boichi.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Boichi Draws Dr. Stone Spinoff Manga About Byakuya (Updated) |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-20/boichi-draws-dr-stone-spinoff-manga-about-byakuya/.152324 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=November 27, 2019 |date=October 20, 2019}}</ref> Like with the main series, the spin-off was also released on Shueish's Manga Plus service. Viz Media also publishes the series on its ''Shonen Jump'' digital platform.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Valdez |first1=Nick |title=Read: Dr. Stone Spin-Off Manga Launches |url=http://comicbook.com/anime/2019/10/27/dr-stone-reboot-byakuya-spin-off-manga-read-free-manga-online/ |website=Comic Book |accessdate=November 27, 2019 |date=October 27, 2019}}</ref> The series finished on December 23, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u9ebb\u751f\u5468\u4e00\u306e\u8aad\u307f\u5207\u308a\u304c\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\u306b\u3001\u6b21\u53f7\u306f\u85e4\u5dfb\u5fe0\u4fca\u304c\u6642\u4ee3\u5287\u3082\u306e\u3067\u767b\u5834 |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/360650 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=January 26, 2020 |language=ja |date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Anime===\n{{seealso|List of Dr. Stone episodes}}\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation was announced in the 51st issue of ''Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump'' on November 19, 2018.<ref name=\"anime\">{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Manga Gets TV Anime Starring Y\u016bsuke Kobayashi in Summer 2019|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-18/dr-stone-manga-gets-tv-anime-starring-yusuke-kobayashi-in-summer-2019/.139502|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=November 18, 2018|date=November 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.funimation.com/forum/topic/18680/master-thread-dr-stone-dubbed|title=[Master Thread] Dr. STONE (Dubbed)|last=Funimation|website=funimation.com|url-status=|access-date=20 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.otakucineasta.com/post/dr-stone-finalmente-foi-lancado|title=Dr. Stone: Finalmente foi lan\u00e7ado!|website=Otaku Cineasta|language=pt|url-status=|access-date=16 July 2019}}</ref> The series is animated by [[TMS Entertainment]], with Shinya Iino as director, Yuichiro Kido as scriptwriter, and Yuko Iwasa as character designer. [[Tatsuya Kato]], Hiroaki Tsutsumi, and Yuki Kanesaka composed the series' music.<ref name=\"staff\">{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Anime Reveals Main Staff, New Visual|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-17/dr-stone-anime-reveals-main-staff-new-visual/.144571|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=March 17, 2019|date=March 17, 2019}}</ref> The series aired from July 5 to December 13, 2019 on [[Tokyo MX]] and other channels.<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Anime Reveals Promo Video, Teaser Visual, 3 New Cast Members|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-12-22/dr-stone-anime-reveals-promo-video-teaser-visual-3-new-cast-members/.141199|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=December 22, 2018|date=December 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Valdez |first1=Nick |title='Dr. Stone' Anime Releases First Teaser |url=https://comicbook.com/anime/2018/12/22/dr-stone-anime-teaser-jump-festa/ |website=ComicBook |accessdate=December 26, 2018 |date=December 22, 2018}}</ref> It ran for 24 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Anime to Have 24 Episodes|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2019-07-07/dr-stone-anime-to-have-24-episodes/.148744|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=July 7, 2019|date=July 7, 2019}}</ref> The first opening theme is \"Good Morning World!\" by Burnout Syndromes, while the series' first ending theme is \"Life\" by Rude-\u03b1.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Anime Reveals Theme Song Artists, July 5 Debut|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-06-02/dr-stone-anime-reveals-theme-song-artists-july-5-debut/.147376|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=June 2, 2019|date=June 2, 2019}}</ref> The second opening theme is \"Sangenshoku\" by Pelican Fanclub, while the series' second ending theme is \"Yume No Youna\" by Saeki YouthK.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pelican Fanclub, Saeki YouthK Perform New Theme Songs for Dr. Stone Anime|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-09-01/pelican-fanclub-saeki-youthk-perform-new-theme-songs-for-dr-stone-anime/.150619|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=September 1, 2019|date=September 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA second season of the anime adaptation was announced after the first season's finale.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Dr. STONE Season 2 release date: Anime sequel confirmed! Episode 24\u2019s ending to begin Stone Wars |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/dr-stone-season-2-release-date-episode-24-ending-stone-wars/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=December 12, 2019 |date=December 12, 2019}}</ref> The second season will focus on the story of the \"Stone Wars\" arc from the manga series.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Patrick Frye |title=Dr. STONE Season 2 anime for Stone Wars announced in Weekly Shonen Jump issue 3 of 2020 |url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/anime/dr-stone-season-2-anime-stone-wars-announced-weekly-shonen-jump-issue-3-2020/ |website=[[Monsters and Critics]] |accessdate=December 12, 2019 |date=December 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dr. Stone Anime Gets 2nd Season|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-13/dr-stone-anime-gets-2nd-season/.154312|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=December 13, 2019|date=December 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe series is streamed by [[Crunchyroll]] worldwide outside of Asia,<ref>{{cite web |title=Crunchyroll Streams Dr. Stone Anime in July |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-05-29/crunchyroll-streams-dr-stone-anime-in-july/.147245 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 29, 2019 |date=May 29, 2019}}</ref> and [[Funimation]] is currently airing a [[simuldub]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sherman |first1=Jennifer |title=Funimation Adds Dr. Stone Anime Simuldub to Summer Lineup |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-06-17/funimation-adds-dr-stone-anime-simuldub-to-summer-lineup/.147952 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=June 17, 2019 |date=June 17, 2019}}</ref> The English dub of the anime began airing on [[Adult Swim]]'s [[Toonami]] block on August 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mateo |first1=Alex |title=Toonami Premieres Dr. Stone Anime on August 24 |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-08-16/toonami-premieres-dr-stone-anime-on-august-24/.150142 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=August 16, 2019 |date=August 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe series ranked #15 along with ''[[Keep Your Hands Off Eizouken!]]'' on a list of the top manga of 2018 for male readers put together by ''[[Kono Manga ga Sugoi!]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-12-08/kono-manga-ga-sugoi-reveals-2018-series-ranking-for-male-readers/.125015 |title=Kono Manga ga Sugoi! Reveals 2018's Series Ranking for Male Readers |last=Hodgkins |first=Crystalyn |date=December 8, 2017 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 27, 2018 }}</ref> The series ranked #17 along ''Sweat and Soap'' and ''Heterogenia Linguistico ~Ishuzoku Gengogaku Ny\u016bmon~'' on ''Kono Manga ga Sugoi!'' list of best manga of 2019 for male readers.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Rafael Antonio Pineda |title=Kono Manga ga Sugoi! Editors Unveil 2020 Rankings |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-11/kono-manga-ga-sugoi-editors-unveil-2020-rankings/.154203 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 11, 2019 |date=December 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, ''Dr. Stone'' won the 64th [[Shogakukan Manga Award]] for the ''[[sh\u014dnen manga|sh\u014dnen]]'' category.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sherman |first1=Jennifer |title=Dr. Stone, Age 12, More Win 64th Shogakukan Manga Awards |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-21/dr-stone-age-12-more-win-64th-shogakukan-manga-awards/.142363 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |date=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2019, [[Crunchyroll]] listed ''Dr. Stone'' in their \"Top 25 best anime of the 2010s\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wolf |first1=Ian |title=Crunchyroll Names The Top 100 Anime of the 2010s |url=http://animeuknews.net/2019/11/crunchyroll-names-the-top-100-anime-of-the-2010s/ |website=Anime UK News |accessdate=November 27, 2019 |date=November 27, 2019}}</ref> [[IGN]] also listed ''Dr. Stone'' among the best anime series of the 2010s.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Best Anime of the Decade (2010 - 2019) |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2020/01/01/best-anime-of-the-decade-2010-2019 |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=January 4, 2020 |date=January 1, 2020}}</ref> ''Dr. Stone'' was the 8th most watched anime series on [[Netflix]] in Japan in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Morrissy |first1=Kim |title=Ultraman Tops Netflix's Most Watched Anime in Japan in 2019 |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-12-31/ultraman-tops-netflix-most-watched-anime-in-japan-in-2019/.154902 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=December 31, 2019 |date=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n''Gadget Ts\u016bshin'' listed Senku's catchphrase \"This is exhilarating!\" in their 2019 anime buzzwords list.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2019-12-04/demon-slayer-dr-stone-zombie-land-saga-buzzwords-make-gadget-tsushin-2019-list/.153903|title=Demon Slayer, Dr. Stone, Zombie Land Saga Buzzwords Make Gadget Ts\u016bshin 2019 List|work=[[Anime News Network]]|first1=Lynzee|last1=Loveridge|first2=Kim|last2=Morrissy|date=December 4, 2019|accessdate=December 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://dr-stone.jp/|Anime official website}} {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{ann|manga|20337}}\n\n{{Series in Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump |state=collapsed}}\n{{Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump - 2010\u20132019 |state=collapsed}}\n{{Shogakukan Manga Award - Sh\u014dnen}}\n{{TMS Entertainment}}\n{{Toonami-anime}}\n\n[[Category:Fiction set in the 6th millennium]]\n[[Category:Adventure anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Anime series based on manga]]\n[[Category:Post-apocalyptic anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Science fiction anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n[[Category:Shueisha manga]]\n[[Category:TMS Entertainment]]\n[[Category:Toonami]]\n[[Category:Viz Media manga]]\n[[Category:Winners of the Shogakukan Manga Award for sh\u014dnen manga]]\n", "name_user": "Pazio Paz", "label": "safe", "comment": "Number of published volumes.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr._Stone"}
{"title_page": "Iran System encoding", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=July 2019}}\n'''Iran System encoding''' was an 8-bit [[character encoding]] scheme and was created by [[Iran System corporation]] for [[Persian language]] support. This encoding was in use in [[Iran]] in [[DOS]]-based programs and after the introduction of Microsoft [[code page 1256]] this encoding became obsolete. However, some [[Windows]] and DOS programs using this encoding are still in use and some Windows fonts with this encoding exist. Now most programs use code page 1256 or [[Unicode]].\n\n==Character set==\nOnly the upper half (128&ndash;255) of the table is shown, the lower half (0&ndash;127) being plain [[ASCII]]. This character set encodes distinct visual forms separately.\n\n{|{{chset-tableformat}}\n{{chset-table-header|IRAN SYSTEM<ref>http://sofia.nmsu.edu/~mleisher/Software/csets/IRANSYSTEM.TXT</ref>}}\n|-\n!{{chset-left2|8_<br/>128}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F0|[[\u06f0]]|128}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F1|[[\u06f1]]|129}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F2|[[\u06f2]]|130}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F3|[[\u06f3]]|131}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F4|[[\u06f4]]|132}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F5|[[\u06f5]]|133}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F6|[[\u06f6]]|134}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F7|[[\u06f7]]|135}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F8|[[\u06f8]]|136}}\n|{{chset-color-digit}}|{{chset-cell|06F9|[[\u06f9]]|137}}\n|{{chset-color-punct}}|{{chset-cell|060C|[[\u060c]]|138}}\n|{{chset-color-letter}}|{{chset-cell|0640|[[\u0640]]|139}}\n|{{chset-color-punct}}|{{chset-cell|061F|[[\u061f]]|140}}\n|{{chset-color-letter}}|{{chset-cell|FE81|[[\ufe81]]|141}}\n|{{chset-color-letter}}|{{chset-cell|FE8B|[[\ufe8b]]|142|fn=\u2020}}\n|{{chset-color-letter}}|{{chset-cell|FE80|[[\ufe80]]|143}}\n|-\n!{{Chset-left2|9_<br/>144}}\n|{{chset-color-letter}}|{{chset-cell|FE8D|[[\ufe8d]]|144}}\n|{{chset-color-le